  0 0x00000000 0x00000000 2017 2018         ascii Terrain descriptions\r\n\r\nDesert\r\n\r\n*Tees\r\nThe best place to start a hole, whether building or playing.  Gourmet grasses on a level, packed-earth foundation.  \r\n*Green\r\nHighest quality bentgrass cradles approach shots and provides a fair test for putters (press <tab> for tricky green).        \r\n*Sand Trap\r\nSculpted trenches filled with clean, raked sand make for a moderately deadly hazard.  Weekend duffers beware (press <tab> to rotate).\r\n*Desert\r\nWho needs hazards when the course is surrounded by desert?  Stops drives short and makes second shots less predictable. \r\n*Pot Bunker\r\nAs hazards go, this is Sand Trap's evil twin.  Deeper trench, heavier sand, harder to get out safely.  Yuck. \r\n*Ravine\r\nA waterless stream where balls roll in and stay for awhile.  Players lose a stroke without hitting a shot.       \r\n*Water\r\nThis would-be oasis turns out to be a mirage that gobbles up poor shots.  Penalty stroke is definitely not an illusion.    \r\n*Joshua Tree\r\nArms outstretched, this hazard beckons players to a better place.  Shoulda stayed in the fairway (press <tab> to size).\r\n*Cactus\r\nEasier to give this porcupine a big hug than to try and hit past it (press <tab> to size).\r\n*Palm Tree\r\nThick-trunked umbrellas provide needed shade for players just hacking through (press <tab> to size).  \r\n*Fairway\r\nCross-cut and bright green target for well-placed drives.  Usually provides a perfect lie for approach shots.\r\n*Firm Fairway\r\nMore freeway than fairway, shots hit here get an extra-high bounce and keep on truckin'.\r\n*Rough\r\nThick green spaghetti usually seen lining fairways, waiting to grab shots that stray off-line.  At least it's green.   \r\n*Waste bunker\r\nUgly brush growing wildly out of a coarse sand bunker gives the players something extra to curse.  \r\n*Brush\r\nDry, half-dead tangle of weed.  Impossible lie.  Drive killer.  Makes players consider bowling instead.  \r\n*Rocks\r\nPlayers witness the dreaded pinball effect if shots land here.  Evil lie and unpredictable, if entertaining, bounce.  
